# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js project with TypeScript. Here's the main structure:

- `src/app/` - Contains the main application code
  - `page.tsx` - The main page component
  - `layout.tsx` - The root layout component
  - `globals.css` - Global styles
  - `favicon.ico` - Site favicon

- Configuration files:
  - `next.config.ts` - Next.js configuration
  - `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration
  - `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS configuration
  - `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint configuration

The application follows Next.js 13+ App Router conventions. The main entry point is [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx), which is wrapped by the root layout in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).

Global styles are defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) and are imported in the root layout.
